annotationA: F-box and WD repeat domain containing 5 (Fbw5) targets proteins for destruction via its role as a substrate receptor for the CRL4 E3 ubiquitin ligase. A key target of Fbw5 is the gig subunit of the Tuberous Sclerosis complex, an important negative regulator of cellular growth via inhibition of the TOR kinase pathway
annotationB: Cullin 4 is the molecular scaffold for the CRL4 E3 ubiquitin ligase complex, which catalyzes the ubiquitylation and subsequent destruction of proteins that function in cell growth and proliferation as well as transcription, replication and repair of the genome; Belongs to the cullin family
